## AI Service — FastAPI + Gemini 2.5 Flash

### Entry Point: [app.py](file:///c:/Users/Dell/Desktop/Mini%20Project/Code/Ai-tasks/app.py)

Three routers mounted:
- `/recipe` — Image → Recipe pipeline
- `/questions` — AI health question generation
- `/recipe` (stream) — Streaming recipe variant

### LangGraph Recipe Pipeline ([recipe_graph.py](file:///c:/Users/Dell/Desktop/Mini%20Project/Code/Ai-tasks/graphs/recipe_graph.py))

A 3-node **LangGraph** `StateGraph` with conditional routing:

```mermaid
graph TD
    V[Validate Images] -->|valid + has images| E[Extract Ingredients]
    V -->|valid + no images| G[Generate Recipe]
    V -->|invalid| END1[END]
    E -->|valid| G
    E -->|invalid| END2[END]
    G --> END3[END]
```

1. **Validate** — Strict food image classification (FOOD / INGREDIENTS / COOKING / NOT_FOOD) with confidence threshold ≥ 0.7
2. **Extract** — Identifies specific ingredients from validated food images
3. **Generate** — Creates a personalized recipe based on user profile, ingredients, dietary preferences, and budget

### AI Config: [gemini.py](file:///c:/Users/Dell/Desktop/Mini%20Project/Code/Ai-tasks/config/gemini.py)
- **Vision model**: `gemini-2.5-flash` (via `google.generativeai`)
- **Text LLM**: `gemini-2.5-flash` (via `langchain_google_genai`, temperature 0.4)

### Legacy File: [photos.py](file:///c:/Users/Dell/Desktop/Mini%20Project/Code/Ai-tasks/photos.py)
An earlier standalone FastAPI app for recipe generation (likely superseded by the LangGraph pipeline). Contains a syntax error on line 2 (`COR+SMiddleware`).

